@database "Footnote Guide"
@author "Heiko Schr÷der"
@$VER: 3.0 (Release 3)
@wordwrap

@node Main "Footnote V1.0"
                               @{" < Table of contents" link "Macro-Package.guide/Main"}

         !!! This Macro only works with ╗Final Writer 97½ !!!

@{fg shine}Benifits:@{fg text}
   Every one has known of this function and many have, up to now painfully
   missed it. Here it is now, Footnote administration for FW97. One declares
   a fixed concept in the current text and one like it for the end.

   So far this was only possibble as an index at the end of documents. With
   this macro comes the concept of a footnote message per page.

@{fg shine}Requirements:@{fg text}
   ╗Final Writer 97½ or later
   The text, must not be in text frames.

@{fg shine}Using the @{"macro" system "Sys:Utilities/Multiview PUBSCREEN=FINALWRITERPUBSCREEN Footnote.iff"}:@{fg text}
  (Screenshot opens at PubScreen of Final Writer)

   @{fg fill}I@{fg text}nsert foot note
      To begin there is only this button available.
      Put the cursor under the concept in the text to be used in the foot note.
      The things near to it will be highlighted. Now press the button.

      The field "Footnote text" will activate.
      Here give the Text wanted.
      Press ╗ENTER½ to approve the wanted text.

      If you have given text a section will appear, in this
      the information for the assistant to work will be written.
      The section has got the name @{fg shine}FNż@{fg text}+Section name.
      Please do not alter this Section. If you do there can be NO GUARANTEE
      that this macro will work.

      Where you placed the cursor a character will be written
      (recognizable as: żNumber)

   @{fg fill}D@{fg text}elete Footnote
      Mark the footnote, that you want to be deleted.
      (recognizable as: żNumber)
      When you press the button, the footnote that was marked will be deleted.

      If no character is selected, the assistant will ask if you want ALL
      characters told be deleted. If you allow this all the footnotes in the
      current section wil be deleted.

   @{fg fill}C@{fg text}reate Footnote
      You should choose this function when you a have completed your document.

      After a request the document will always first be saved under the original
      name. Then the footnotes with the @{"preferences data" link "Voreinst"} will be written and
      all FNżSections are deleted.
      If this has worked the document will be finished and saved with the
      ending ".FNote". The Footnotes are thus completed.

      The assistant will also ask you to save the file as a ".FNote" which you
      should use, should you wish to modify the document.
      Any characters left by the assistant will then be deleted and all foot-
      notes created.

                     - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

   In the lowest part of the windows you will find the Preferences settings.
   This can be modified through the Menu:@{fg fill}Project | @{"Preferences..." link "Voreinst"}@{fg text}

                     - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

   @{fg fill}ESC@{fg text} or closing the window.
      Terminates the Macro.

                     - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

@{fg shine}Hint:@{fg text}
      If the macro gives problems, the macro will not start or something
      similiar, so delete the preferences file @{fg shine}"S:FW_Footnote.prefs"@{fg text}.
      This should solve most problems.

@{fg shine}Warning:@{fg text}
      If you write a document containing the character: "ż" the assistant will
      always throw up problems.
      These characters are very IMPORTANT for the Footnote assistant and
      should be avoided.

@endnode

@node Voreinst "Preferences for the Footnote assistant"

   With this you can the edit the preferences file for the Footnote assistant.

   @{fg fill}N@{fg text}umbering:
      You can choose between
         - per page
         - continuously
      With this you can choose whether the footnote numbering is for each page,
      or is continuous.

   @{fg fill}F@{fg text}ont:
      Here you select the Font to be used for the footnotes.

   Font si@{fg fill}z@{fg text}e:
      Here you give the size of the font for the footnotes, this should be
      smaller than the body text.
      The Number will ALWAYS be "super" text.

   @{fg fill}O@{fg text}utput:
      Here you give the format for the Footnote.
      %F = symbol for the number of the Footnote

      !!! Please don't use quotation marks. !!!

      A few examples:

                     *%F
         Example 1:   *1  Declare the Footnote
                      *2  Declare...

                     %F) -
         Example 2:   1) -  Declare the Footnote
                      2) -  Declare...

   @{fg fill}L@{fg text}ine length :
      Here you set the length of the line seperating the body text from the
      footnote text.

   @{fg fill}I@{fg text}ndent:
      With this you can choose what indent should get very long
      descriptions (more than one line).

   Spee@{fg fill}d@{fg text}:
      To speed up the addition of the footnotes in "fast" mode the view zoom is
      set to 20% otherwise the current zoom is used.

                     - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

   @{fg fill}S@{fg text}ave
      The settings will be save to the file@{fg fill}"S:FW_Footnote.prefs"@{fg text} and will
      be used any time you start the Macro.

   @{fg fill}A@{fg text}pply
      The current settings will only be used until you terminate the macro.
      When you restart the macro the old preferences will be used.


   @{fg fill}C@{fg text}ancel
      All preferences will return to their last used state.

@endnode
